  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_56142ccbd67c6291bf4860f454bff8e5" level="item"><did><unittitle>Large scrapbook compiled by Mrs. A.E.M. Hasbrouck and presented to the Ithaca Woman's Club in 1928. Contains typed history of the Club, list of Charter and Earliest Members for as far as was known at that date, photographs of:</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1928/1928">1928</unitdate><container id="aspace_2c9800840c61c9f441188192d585518e" label="Mixed Materials [31924064919065]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_c18c82a4f8f1c2271e8b258065e3af12"><head>Scope and Contents</head><list type="ordered"><item>Mrs. Hasbrouck</item><item>Mrs. Charles Crandall</item><item>Miss Charity Smith</item><item>Mrs. Louisa Riley (2) and her home on University Avenue</item><item>The Lewis Home, 444 N. Aurora St. (where Club was organized)</item></list><p>Later photographs include:</p><list type="ordered"><item>Mrs. Jamie Messenger</item><item>Juanita B. Bates</item><item>Mrs. J.A. Winans</item><item>Lelle Rhodes Mangang</item><item>Mary M. Denton</item><item>Mrs. Sidney L. Howell</item><item>Sarah L. Osborn</item><item>Viola B. Lent</item><item>Maude Coleman Walker</item><item>Margaret L. Head</item><item>Mrs. Thomas J. Parker</item><item>Alice D. Smiley</item><item>Anna Ball Cary (Mrs. Elmer E.)</item><item>Gratia Mungle</item><item>Isabel B. Doyle</item><item>Mrs. Alfred H. Butwell</item><item>Mrs. David Perry</item><item>Minnie W. Muenscher</item><item>Veta A. Butterworth</item><item>Mrs. A.L. Winsor</item><item>and groups.</item></list><p>(All the foregoing were presidents.)</p><p> This scrapbook also contains copies of the presidents' speeches and brochures of the club through various years. The first program is dated 1896-1897 and series runs through to 1948-1949.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_9bdf8832a5901d5a28faebdfe5930a4d" level="file"><did><unittitle>"New Crusader" Yearbooks + Journal Writeups</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian